  "question": "Carlos is planting a lemon tree. The tree will cost $90 to plant. Each year it will grow 7 lemons, which he can sell for $1.5 each. It costs $3 a year to water and feed the tree. How many years will it take before he starts earning money on the lemon tree?",
  "prompt": "Carlos is planting a lemon tree. The tree will cost $90 to plant. Each year it will grow 7 lemons, which he can sell for $1.5 each. It costs $3 a year to water and feed the tree. How many years will it take before he starts earning money on the lemon tree?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "13",
  "generated_text": "To determine how many years it will take before Carlos starts earning money, we need to compare the costs incurred up to a specific year with the revenue generated up to that same year.\n\n1.  **Analyze the costs and revenue:**\n    *   **Planting Cost:** $\\$90$ (One-time initial cost).\n    *   **Annual Cost:** $\\$3$ per year for water and feed.\n    *   **Annual Revenue:** $7$ lemons $\\times \\$1.5$ per lemon = $\\$10.50$ per year.\n\n2.  **Determine the condition for \"starting to earn money\":**\n    \"Starting to earn money\" means the cumulative revenue exceeds the cumulative costs up to that year.\n    Let $n$ be the number of years.\n    *   Total Cost after $n$ years = $90 + 3n$.\n    *   Total Revenue after $n$ years = $10.5n$.\n\n    We need to find the smallest integer $n$ such that:\n    $$10.5n > 90 + 3n$$\n\n3.  **Solve the inequality:**\n    Subtract $3n$ from both sides:\n    $$7.5n > 90$$\n\n    Divide by $7.5$:\n    $$n > \\frac{90}{7.5}$$\n    $$n > 12$$\n\n4.  **Verify the result:**\n    *   **At $n = 11$ years:**\n        Cost = $90 + (11 \\times 3) = 90 + 33 = \\$123$.\n        Revenue = $11 \\times 10.5 = \\$115.5",
  "pred_answer": "115.5",
